The paper discusses modifications to the AlphaZero algorithm to support multiplayer environments, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the approach in two simple 3-player games, which falls under game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of AlphaZero in real-world applications, which could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
